# Exceptions
#
# -modernize-use-trailing-return-type
#
#  We disable this as AUTOSAR does not allow for non-template trailing return
#  types, and this check does not have this sort of granularity.
#
# -modernize-use-default-member-init
# -readability-redundant-member-init
#
#  We disable this as AUTOSAR requires the use of redundant member
#  initializers to ensure explicit initialization. In addition, they do not
#  allow for mixed initializers. Either all members are initialized using
#  default member initialization, or none of them are.
#
# -cert-dcl21-cpp
#
#  We disable this as AUTOSAR does not require this, and it is mutually
#  exclusive with readability-const-return-type, which identifies a known
#  performance issue.
#
# -cert-oop54-cpp
#
#  This produces a false positive when assignment is implemented using the
#  temporary swap method, which AUTOSAR requires.
#
# -readability-avoid-const-params-in-decls
#
#  We disable this as AUTOSAR requires that all params that are not changed
#  be marked as const, even if they do not contribute to the function
#  signature.
#
# -readability-static-accessed-through-instance
#
#  We disable this as AUTOSAR requires that functions that can be made static
#  are made static. Requiring this would be too much of a code change, and
#  does not always work with templates
#
# -modernize-concat-nested-namespaces
#
#  Perforce currently does not support this. Once it does, we can remove this
#

